<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-11-07T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-11-07T20:00:00-05:00" n="717" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d717">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">761.9411/66a: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-07T20:00:00-05:00">November 7,
                                1940—8 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>453. The American Legation at Tehran telegraphs under date November 6<note n="94" xml:id="d717fn94">Telegram No. 242, not printed.</note> that
                        according to a Soviet source Japan and Russia are about to conclude some
                        kind of agreement regarding respective spheres of influence in eastern
                        Asia.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>